<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="stage-n">stage <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /steɪdʒ/    美 /steɪdʒ/  </p>
<p>[C]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>舞台：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When the superstar appeared on the stage, all the audience stood up to applaud.
当这位巨星出现在舞台上时，所有的观众都站起来鼓掌。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-the">2.★ <strong>[与the连用] 戏剧表演：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>For him the stage is just a means of making a living.
对他来说，戏剧表演只是谋生的手段。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>时期；阶段</strong></h4>
<p>one part of the progress or development of sth：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>at different stages of development
在不同的发展时期</p></div></div>